brewery.brewery_description: Alewerks Brewing Company is located in the heart of the early colonies in Williamsburg, Virginia. Established in 2006 we have rolled out a broad range of beer offerings and quickly established a reputation for fine beer. We operate a direct fired brick-clad Peter Austin brew house and ferment all our beers in state-of-the-art conical fermentors.

beer.beer_description: American Pale ale with citrus aroma, deft balance, and abundant hop finish.
American Pale ale with citrus aroma, deft balance, and abundant hop finish.
A powerfully robust American porter with rich character.
This amber colored ale is loaded with Pumpkin pie aroma and flavor. It actually does taste like Pumpkin pie! At 7.3% ABV, it will keep you warm on a cool Autumn eve.
Rich Milk-Stout with a healthy amount of Guatemala Antigua coffee.
Complex yet mellow American Brown Ale brewed with six malt varieties.
Our Double IPA is loaded with Pacific Northwest hops blended with a light malt backbone. A bitter Valentine for you to love, however unrequited.
American Pale ale with citrus aroma, deft balance, and abundant hop finish.
Ambitiously-hopped American IPA with notes of passion fruit and mango.

We age a stronger version of our Coffeehouse Stout in Virginia Gentlemen Bourbon Barrels for three months. This aging adds layers of complexity including notes of vanilla and Bourbon to this big coffee beer.

Golden in color with an intense citrusy, floral aroma due to a lengthy dry hop process. Expect flavors of citrus, fruit, light malt, hints of powdered sugar, and American hops. Finishes clean and dry with a smack of hoppy goodness.

An Imperial Porter, brewed with Caribbean unrefined sugar and aged for two months in Virginia Gentleman Bourbon barrels. The Porter's traditional flavors of coffee, chocolate, and caramel are complemented by vanilla and hints of bourbon.
You just may fall in love with this DIPA. Its intense hop kick comes from a healthy dose of Mosaic hops.
Powerful hop character for when you want to enjoy more than one.
Traditional Belgian-style Witbier brewed with coriander and orange peel.
Intricately smooth and classically inspired Munich-style Helles Lager.
Red in color with aromas of dark fruit and caramel malt, flavors of caramel, fruit, plums, and a hint of roast, ending with a dry, lightly hopped finish.
Old Stitch is based on a 17th century recipe developed by Frank Clark at Colonial Williamsburg.
A powerfully robust American porter with rich character.
Our annually released Barleywine changes every year depending on what mood we're in. It is, however, always a "big" beer usually around 10% ABV. Enjoy now or cellar for a special occasion.
Spiced wheat ale brewed for Colonial Williamsburg
An Imperial Porter brewed with a Haitian sugar called Rapadou. Rapadou is a traditionally processed cane sugar that lends a great toffee caramel flavor to our 9% ABV Porter.

Springhouse is an aged Belgian Saison (Farmhouse Ale). It pours gold-amber, is will carbonated but has a small to non existent head, and has a sweet fruity aroma with apples, green grapes and apricots the dominant taste.

Our first foray into the "wild" world of brewing. We aged this Belgian-style ale in red wine barrels with Brettanomyces, Lactobaccilus, and Pediococcus for 18 months. The result is a tart, funky, and complex beer that is still quite easy on the palate. Enjoy from your favorite chalice at 45-50 degrees Fahrenheit.
A pitch black imperial stout with dozens of pounds of chocolate added before resting on roasted cocoa nibs for a decadently bittersweet dark chocolate experience.
German style tart wheat ale with tropical character and tart citric punch. Summer seasonal.
This winter warmer is perfect for a cold day. Brewed with vanilla, cinnamon and other spices.

Our take on a Belgian-style Tripel is named after the schooner "Atlantic". This gorgeous vessel achieved 20 knots during her sea trials in 1903. Expect aromas of banana, light clove, and pear followed by flavors of apricot, spicy esters, and pear. This beer has a light sweetness but finishes dry with a touch of hop attitude.
